main event: Two objects resembling a blimp were observed in the sky over Marietta, Ohio on June 10-12, 1966, lasting for 3-5 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were described as having brightness comparable to a fluorescent light bulb., The witnesses reported that the objects resembled blimps without fins and were not shiny., The objects appeared to stand still at times and changed shape during the observation., The sighting was made by five witnesses in a location familiar to them for identifying aerial phenomena., The report concluded that nothing indicated the objects could not have been civilian aircraft.
witness description: civilian observers familiar with the area
